{"key":"processedPost-10086287","value":{"id":10086287,"first":10082852,"last":10097794,"when":1238603103,"utime":"04/01/09 07:25 PM","content":"Make darn sure you air up the bike tire to around 50 to 60 psi before using each time.&nbsp; If the tire is soft, the jar will compress it right to the rim, and shatter your jar, which makes a horrible mess of your colonized grains all over the floor.&nbsp; I'm sure you guys who use bike tires have already learned this the hard way, but for the new growers, be advised.&nbsp; Keep a tire pump right next to the tire, because they'll lose pressure after a few days.<br />RR","title":"Re: Breaking up fully colonized jars","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}